 it down into easy bite-sized nuggets that you can implement into your cleaning routine every single week. Now I will say we're at like 18,000 subscribers, something like that, and our goal by the end of this month is to reach 20,000 subscribers and then we're going to do a giveaway. So if you want to sign up and help us reach that goal plus get all of this cleaning knowledge delivered to your inbox every single week, all you got to do is comment the word newsletter and I'll see you over there.", "history": [{"date": "2026-07-18", "plays": 54545, "likes": 1116, "comments": 1064}, {"date": "2026-07-19", "plays": 54956, "likes": 1124, "comments": 1073}], "still_climbing": false, "hook_type": "Education", "is_relevant": true}, {"shortCode": "Dav32l1hNAN", "url": "https://www.instagram.com/p/Dav32l1hNAN/", "caption": "Cleaning up my daughters shoes", "timestamp": "2026-07-13T21:24:35.000Z", "videoDuration": 56.91, "videoPlayCount": 87899, "videoViewCount": null, "likesCount": 2552, "commentsCount": 20, "displayUrl": "https://scontent-iad3-2.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/745011505_18443838799140899_7577029075806263408_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_p1080x1080_sh2.08_tt6&_nc_ht=scontent-iad3-2.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=111&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gG7AF56MhBN4ZH4PGX36ol0f8LkVeMAZMiYh-72_fDZi9kOP_pdDtUwT5pA8nA_GhQ&_nc_ohc=niAzbT3pP6YQ7kNvwH4umtS&_nc_gid=qI6WPGN-knSWDgTm-Fd67Q&edm=ADp7STQBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AQCgBKfX2iYAp1aL3Cx31TyOrqrkUzuYVvoXuYUMjABwIw&oe=6A620764&_nc_sid=c6f216", "videoUrl": "https://scontent-lax3-2.cdninstagram.com/o1/v/t2/f2/m86/AQPu9T8r0J4_SDvzh0b2nmvoYSQqsy_vs5Jf8MTcmPDeOj9_z_kN7v1u_W-sABcuV7EWBrTI_0Rw6oMY9Z1GpAWE--ikqQxelTKA7M4.mp4?_nc_cat=100&_nc_sid=5e9851&_nc_ht=scontent-lax3-2.cdninstagram.com&_nc_ohc=Qw0pKLVzG-sQ7kNvwH8r2yw&efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6Inhwdl9wcm9ncmVzc2l2ZS5JTlNUQUdSQU0uQ0xJUFMuQzMuNzIwLmRhc2hfYmFzZWxpbmVfMV92MSIsInhwdl9hc3NldF9pZCI6OTEwNDgzMjc1NDE4NTI2LCJhc3NldF9hZ2VfZGF5cyI6NSwidmlfdXNlY2FzZV9pZCI6MTAwOTksImR1cmF0aW9uX3MiOjU2LCJ1cmxnZW5fc291cmNlIjoid3d3In0%3D&ccb=17-1&vs=7bb4fc0ea8e70199&_nc_&_nc_gid=jKDDfSOcP8a6wFM7cq5Bcw&_nc_ss=7ca8c&_nc_zt=28&oh=00_AQArNtPQI9xzaVbZteEyh1RKFYp4_RpcPgsR-JUmlDc9zg&oe=6A5DFCDD", "musicInfo": {"artist_name": "cleanthatup", "song_name": "Original audio", "uses_original_audio": true, "should_mute_audio": false, "should_mute_audio_reason": "", "audio_id": "27760039500349481"}, "ownerUsername": "cleanthatup", "ownerFullName": "Brandon Pleshek", "transcript": "My daughter grew out of her very first pair of chucks, so let's get them nice and clean so we can donate them. The first thing I like to do is remove the laces, grab a bowl, fill it up with some warm water, and add a little OxiClean. This will make those dirty laces nice and white again. For the shoes, I found that Dawn Power Wash does a great job to not only clean the soles, but also the canvas too. I spray the shoes down, then I come through with a soft bristle brush and give everything a good scrub. This little brush is actually really handy, and I found it at the dollar store. I think it's a vegetable brush, but it works great for shoes. Then I give everything a good rinse, make sure to scrub the insides as well, rinse again to make sure there's no soap residue left behind. After cleaning, I did notice some scuff marks on both the toes and soles of the shoe, so for this I like to use a magic eraser, give them a quick scrub down, and then rinse with a damp towel, and they were completely gone. To get them dry as quickly as possible, I just wrap them up in a few towels. Now this was definitely the most satisfying part of the job. These laces were really dirty, as you can see in the water, but they absolutely cleaned up great. Now these chucks are nice and clean and ready for their next journey.", "history": [{"date": "2026-07-18", "plays": 87187, "likes": 2530, "comments": 20}, {"date": "2026-07-19", "plays": 87883, "likes": 2551, "comments": 20}], "still_climbing": false, "hook_type": "Personal Experience", "is_relevant": true