"Now in my experience of cleaning a ton of kitchen cabinets, there's usually always one that is the most greasy and dirty. You might have guessed it already, but that's the one above your oven and hood range. And I like to suggest using a degreaser. Now the one I like to recommend is just simple Dawn dish soap, not the other fancy kinds, just the basic blue Dawn, because this is going to do a great job to break that down. What I like to do is just add a little bit of Dawn to a warmed up scrub mommy, and then give that area a really good scrub. Now you don't have to scrub too hard here, just let the Dawn do the work of breaking down all the grease and grime. Now once you feel like it's nice and clean, then always come through, rinse it really well, and make sure to dry the surface. Now you might be wondering why don't we just use Dawn to clean all of the cabinets, and in my experience, repeated use of Dawn on wood surfaces has the tendency to kind of dry things out and can potentially cause damage, and we don't want that. So I really only use it when I need it on these specialty cases and on those areas that have a really bad grease and grime build up.", "history": [{"date": "2026-07-18", "plays": 68634, "likes": 1472, "comments": 13}, {"date": "2026-07-19", "plays": 68803, "likes": 1475, "comments": 13}], "still_climbing": false, "hook_type": "Personal Experience", "is_relevant": true}, {"shortCode": "DaLxwFrzS_s", "url": "https://www.instagram.com/p/DaLxwFrzS_s/", "caption": "#cloroxpartner Try this @clorox bleach hack to keep your flowers fresh and lasting longer!", "timestamp": "2026-06-29T21:00:39.000Z", "videoDuration": 65.501, "videoPlayCount": 87189, "videoViewCount": 31765, "likesCount": 1911, "commentsCount": 41, "displayUrl": "https://scontent-lax3-2.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/730051458_18441411031140899_1333103500934177354_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_p1080x1080_sh2.08_tt6&_nc_ht=scontent-lax3-2.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=111&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gGx3muaWDKHRcyMtqra-8qAM7d2-lZSSBBYG-dmHdOWAevCO6b8M5AIVmesVChIcRo&_nc_ohc=NxRtOiCB5mYQ7kNvwGxLqLO&_nc_gid=CV2mxRlBT0UgRvDTbx4BOg&edm=ADp7STQBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AQCinEyyXJxxrxxlqevD9Pcb54DO6pgGzTTDYqr44xaBxw&oe=6A620D17&_nc_sid=c6f216", "videoUrl": "https://scontent-sea5-1.cdninstagram.com/o1/v/t2/f2/m86/AQNbCO3Zsgfv6098LrTeBjIiAGleUDgQoORgaA_e1VuO7S29On5v5rjC7mgUHhcNoTtg-FUs56cvUIE3eFR4gFt7HezJCOJIPOJZvto.mp4?_nc_cat=103&_nc_sid=5e9851&_nc_ht=scontent-sea5-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_ohc=aO5-DxqbChgQ7kNvwFCscMD&efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6Inhwdl9wcm9ncmVzc2l2ZS5JTlNUQUdSQU0uQ0xJUFMuQzMuNzIwLmRhc2hfYmFzZWxpbmVfMV92MSIsInhwdl9hc3NldF9pZCI6MTIzMTExMTk3OTAyODA4MywiYXNzZXRfYWdlX2RheXMiOjE5LCJ2aV91c2VjYXNlX2lkIjoxMDA5OSwiZHVyYXRpb25fcyI6NjUsInVybGdlbl9zb3VyY2UiOiJ3d3cifQ%3D%3D&ccb=17-1&vs=e21a49ac130fe44b&_nc_-yvBBUCKAJDMywXQFBgAAAAAAAYEmRhc2hfYmFzZWxpbmVfMV92MREAdf4HZeadAQA&_nc_gid=7E8Z5lcZaV-L-LCMDB2Pgw&_nc_ss=72689&_nc_zt=28&oh=00_AQAjHPVDd6XSFgkgnhJByDVZzbDM3AR1Z7aXC94lR_SQbw&oe=6A5DFC04", "musicInfo": {"artist_name": "cleanthatup", "song_name": "Original audio", "uses_original_audio": true, "should_mute_audio": false, "should_mute_audio_reason": "", "audio_id": "28424599287140247"}, "ownerUsername": "cleanthatup", "ownerFullName": "Brandon Pleshek", "transcript": "Now there are some other cool ways that you can use bleach around the house. For instance, let's say you got some fresh, beautiful flowers and you want them to last longer. Now all you need to do is grab your vase and mix up 1 fourth teaspoon of bleach to every one third gallon of water in the vase. Cut your flowers to size and place them inside. The bleach is going to help the flowers last longer and stay fresh. But to show you, I got two of the same bouquet. One is only in water and one is in the mixture and we'll see how long they last. It is now day 11 on the flower test here and we're really starting to see some results. Now the flowers with no bleach added to the water are starting to look a little sad, kind of wilted and just droopy over here. However, the ones with the little bleach in the water are definitely way more vibrant and fresh still. Now I did not adjust the water, add any water to these at all. I wanted to stay at the same level that way I could really see how long they would last. But if you want to at home, you can also just dump this out around the five to six day mark, add some fresh water in there with that little bit of bleach and it can make them last even longer. So the next time you get some fresh flowers, definitely give this hack a try because it really works.", "history": [{"date": "2026-07-18", "plays": 87065, "likes": 1910, "comments": 41}, {"date": "2026-07-19", "plays": 87188, "likes": 1911, "comments": 41}], "still_climbing": false, "hook_type": "Education", "is_relevant": false}, {"shortCode": "DaD9hlvvIsY", "url": "https://www.instagram.com/p/DaD9hlvvIsY/", "caption": "This was so satisfying to clean", "timestamp": "2026-06-26T20:08:15.000Z", "videoDuration": 26.633, "videoPlayCount": 159201, "videoViewCount": 72131, "likesCount": 1826, "commentsCount": 29, "displayUrl": "https://scontent-ord5-3.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.71878-15/730310887_1328318565479830_4834429159672308869_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_tt6&_nc_ht=scontent-ord5-3.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=110&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gHuPKYq65aU_Rl0GrkjTCzvg8ueaTWwnFZppd9BVCgM4UfFllouAgjKHSlztpu4fHc&_nc_ohc=HiVt47RhqQsQ7kNvwE_ADWN&_nc_gid=4dKp5B0byXMYWRjG5Bn8og&edm=ADp7STQBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AQA3ECSUqRE9QWUNRPGwOAxqelxAU3vzIncbfZNbNV-ImA&oe=6A61EC70&_nc_sid=c6f216", "videoUrl": "https://scontent-ord5-3.cdninstagram.com/o1/v/t2/f2/m86/AQNhskZC8dmcOedGg-rrv2HjEoutrSSyuLWfH5vQ3JNfVjP1v3KpY9oqPxIM0-xbScYKt5fbxbW5TpsIVV7GifuwDHZ2QWQPB9E6mS8.mp4?_nc_cat=110&_nc_sid=5e9851&_nc_ht=scontent-ord5-3.cdninstagram.com&_nc_ohc=cFAiHkQuiE8Q7kNvwHdkHua&efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6Inhwdl9wcm9ncmVzc2l2ZS5JTlNUQUdSQU0uQ0xJUFMuQzMuNzIwLmRhc2hfYmFzZWxpbmVfMV92MSIsInhwdl9hc3NldF9pZCI6OTU1NDUwNzkwODgwMjQ1LCJhc3NldF9hZ2VfZGF5cyI6MjIsInZpX3VzZWNhc2VfaWQiOjEwMD