the dust, but the reason you want to do this is when the coils get full of dust and debris, it essentially creates like a dust sweater around them and holds heat in place, so then your refrigerator has to work so much harder to stay cold. Now a nice clean coil is going to easily dissipate all of that heat, and then your compressor won't have to run as often or as long, so then your refrigerator runs more efficient, stays cold, and ultimately saves you money.", "history": [{"date": "2026-07-18", "plays": 178443, "likes": 3898, "comments": 27}, {"date": "2026-07-19", "plays": 178601, "likes": 3900, "comments": 27}], "still_climbing": false, "hook_type": "Problem", "is_relevant": true}]}